title: TOL Summer Crit Series
description: The TOL Summer Crit Series is back again.  Come down to New Braunfels for some good ol`e racing weeknight fun!  With a great course, awesome hosting venue, fun racing, and great people, it\'s a win win for everyone.  Bring the whole family!
course: .8 mile closed course with multiple turns that are tight and sweeping with a couple that are open and fast.  coures is clean with great straight aways out of the turns!
registration: Race day registration opens at 5:00pm and closes 10 minutes before each race.
notes:
Cash only this year, no checks.
All USAC rules apply. Permit applied for.
Teams wheels in/out.
You MUST wear an ANSI approved helmet at all times while on the bike.
NO warm-ups on the course while races are in progress.
Field minimum = 10
Race lengths and start times are approximate and may vary according to the amount of daylight available.
Cat 4 placing in the top 5 2 times in C Race, or winning the C race 2 times in the season are ineligible to enter the C race and must race the B Race.
Registration: Race day registration opens at 5:00pm and closes 10 minutes before each race.
Information: For additional information contact Jean Paul Legault (830) 221-6261 or jeanpaullegault@hotmail.com
directions:
Tree of Life Church
5513 IH 35S
New Braunfels, Texas 78132

From Austin: Take IH 35 South and exit Engel road. Turn left and go under I-35
From San Antoino: Take IH 35 North and exit Engel road.

title: Blazing Saddles, the Afterburn
description:
Blazing Saddles, the Afterburn
6 Hour Race
course: 8 mile loop at Bluff Creek Ranch, how many laps can you do in six hours?
registration: $25 per person, solo or on a team. $30 onsite. USAC license required or one day non-license holder fee of $5 payable onsite.
notes: Men\'s Solo, Women\'s Solo, Men\'s 2 person team, and Women\'s two person team, all pay out 25% to top 40% of entries. Men\'s Solo Open pays out 50% to top 40%.
directions: Bluff Creek Ranch is on Owl Creek Road, 1/2 mile east of Hwy 77 in Warda, Texas.

title: Texas Junior and Masters Regional Track Championsh
Elk Hill Circuit Race
course: 2.5 mile course - smooth asphalt and concrete with the infamous \"Elk Hill\" climb every lap! This circuit includes part of the Thursday Night Crit Series course and a section of the locals\' favorite, a 150-meter, 8 percent grade (aka \"Elk Hill\") on every lap. Bring your climbing legs cause you\'ll need them!
registration: Pre-registration on bikereg.com. Registration on raceday ($10 late fee applies) is also available.
notes: Come join the fun! This race is followed on Sunday by the nearby Rockwall Criteriums. 2 Days of HOT Texas Racing!!
directions: Located east of Dallas off US 80 in Sunnyvale. Exit East Fork Road, turn left at stop sign and cross over highway. Turn right at the stop sign and continue down service road (2-way). At Rebecca Road go left, then continue for 1/2 mile and follow posted signs to parking area.
